How can I sort an array of integers in descending order using C++ code? Please provide an example.
Data Format:
```
#include <iostream>
#include <algorithm>
using namespace std;
int main() {
    int arr[] = {10, 5, 13, 2, 7};
    int n = sizeof(arr)/sizeof(arr[0]);
    // sort array in descending order
    sort(arr, arr + n, greater<int>());
    // print sorted array
    cout << "Sorted Array (Descending Order): ";
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        cout << arr[i] << " ";
    }
    return 0;
}
```
What is the output of the above code?
